Version: 0.1.28
Date: 2026-04-20

Changes:
- Responses/item runtime migration:
  - add item-native transcript types and adapters for messages, function calls,
    function-call outputs, and reasoning items.
  - add an OpenAI Responses provider and make the OpenAI runtime path item-aware.
  - migrate the main loop, query engine, prompt observability, and session
    persistence to use item transcripts and response boundaries.
- Runtime correctness and cleanup:
  - fix empty-stop recovery for item-native tool runs so post-tool final-summary
    recovery still triggers when the provider emits no assistant text item.
  - fix Responses input replay so assistant history is encoded with input_text.
  - attach response-level correlation fields to prompt observability and usage
    logs.
  - remove no-longer-needed message-persistence compatibility paths from
    QueryEngine and session helpers.
- Tests and validation:
  - add unit coverage for runtime items, Responses provider behavior, session
    response boundaries, and item-aware observability.
  - migrate session-resume E2E coverage to item transcript persistence.
  - pin the default E2E model back to moonshotai/kimi-k2.5 to match the
    existing cost baseline.

Validation:
- npm run typecheck
- npm test
- MERLION_COST_GATE=warn npm run test:e2e

Related commits:
- feat(runtime): migrate transcript and provider flow to response items
- fix(runtime): restore empty-stop recovery and response observability
- test(e2e): migrate session resume to item transcripts and repin default model
